#. type: Content of: <guide><abstract>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:22
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "This howto will show you how to set up the Fluxbox window manager for X11.\n"
msgstr "このガイドでは、X11向けのFluxboxウインドウマネージャのセットアップ方法を見ていきます。\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:34
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "はじめに"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:36
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Introduction to the Fluxbox window manager"
msgstr "Fluxboxウインドウマネージャの紹介"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:40
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For those who are unfamiliar with Linux's desktop model, window managers (WMs)\n"
"are the applications which are run by X11 to manage other graphical programs.\n"
"WMs control where each window is placed, its size, and which desktop(s) have\n"
"access to it. This can be done automatically via a set of user-defined rules or\n"
"can be done at runtime with the mouse and possibly keyboard shortcuts,\n"
"depending on the specific WM.\n"
msgstr ""
"ウインドウマネージャは、Linuxのデスクトップモデルに慣れていない人向けに他のグラフィカルプログラムを管理するため、X11で動作しているアプリケーションです。\n"
"これは決して必要というわけではありませんが、ウインドウマネージャが無いX11セッションはひどく醜く、一般に現代のデスクトップに関連した多くの機能が含まれていません。\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:49
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Some WMs, however, take on more functionality than just window management.\n"
"Fluxbox also provides a platform for launching applications, configuring\n"
"keyboard shortcuts and background images, as well as displaying information\n"
"with the slit. GNOME's default WM, Metacity, does not include these things, but\n"
"they are available through other GNOME programs. Thus, one cannot truly say\n"
"that Fluxbox is a lightweight WM. However, since Fluxbox includes everything\n"
"necessary for a basic desktop, many people use it in place of larger desktop\n"
"suites like GNOME or KDE.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:60
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To make things even more confusing, however, Fluxbox can replace the default WM\n"
"for GNOME or KDE. For example, some people find that Metacity, GNOME's window\n"
"manager, simply does not have the flexibility they need, but that Fluxbox does\n"
"not have all the built-in applications and integration they desire from a\n"
"complete desktop environment. Thus, a person could use Fluxbox to manage the\n"
"windows and GNOME for the rest. Note, however, that with this setup there are\n"
"some issues caused by overlapping feature sets.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:70
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Fluxbox can also be expanded by third party software. This is often ideal in\n"
"situations where hardware resources are limited, or even just as a matter of\n"
"personal taste.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:76
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This guide is aimed at those who are new to Fluxbox, curious, or who\n"
"are just wanting to get more out of the Gentoo/Fluxbox experience. This guide\n"
"will also illustrate how to get more (yet quite optional) functionality by\n"
"using third party programs which work well with Fluxbox.\n"
msgstr ""
"このガイドは、Fluxboxを初めて使う人、好奇心のある人、GentooのFluxboxでより多くのことを体験したいだけの人が対象です。\n"
"また、Fluxboxでうまく動作するサードパーティ製プログラムを使って機能を増やす方法(完全に自由選択)も説明します。\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:87
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Installing Fluxbox"
msgstr "Fluxboxのインストール"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:89
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Base installation"
msgstr "標準インストール"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:93
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"First, make sure you've installed a working X environment, as shown in the <uri\n"
"link=\"https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Xorg/Configuration\">X Server Configuration HOWTO</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:98
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Before you install Fluxbox, you should take a look at some of the available USE\n"
"flags.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:103
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"While the <c>gnome</c> and <c>kde</c> USE flags are provided to give\n"
"compatibility with these environments, it has been the author's experience that\n"
"these USE flags are not needed. If you desire qt, gtk+, or any KDE/GNOME utility\n"
"then you are free to emerge and configure those independently. The <c>gnome</c>\n"
"and <c>kde</c> flags simply add support for the respective protocols, and do not\n"
"depend on external libraries. However, they do increase the Fluxbox binary\n"
"size.\n"
msgstr ""
"Gentooは、Fluxboxを素早く簡単にインストールできるようebuildを提供しています。\n"
"GnomeやKDE、Fluxboxといったウインドウマネージャに「互換性」を提供する<c>gnome</c>や<c>kde</c>のようなUSEフラグをGentooは提供していますが、\n"
"著者の経験ではこれらが必要になったことはありません。\n"
"qt、gtk+、あるいはKDE/GNOMEユーティリティをお望みなら、自由にemergeして独立に設定できます。\n"
"例えば、著者はFluxboxでk3b KDE CD-R(W)焼きユーティリティを使っています。\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:113
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"There is also a <c>vim-syntax</c> flag to make configuration easier later on.\n"
"This flag will install <c>fluxbox-syntax</c>, a special Fluxbox color scheme for\n"
"<c>vim</c>. This enables users to more readily see the contents of their keys\n"
"and init files for Fluxbox. It's a tiny extension for vim, so it's highly\n"
"recommended.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:121
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Finally, there are two flags that customize the functionality of Fluxbox,\n"
"<c>slit</c> and <c>toolbar</c>. These flags are provided so that users who don't\n"
"need the <uri\n"
"link=\"http://fluxbox-wiki.org/index.php?title=Faqs#What_is_the_slit\">slit</uri>\n"
"or the <uri link=\"http://fluxbox.org/features/\">toolbar</uri> can compile\n"
"Fluxbox without them. This is useful if you want to run an extremely minimal\n"
"environment, or if you plan to use different applications that provide these\n"
"features, such as standalone panels or docks.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:132
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Once you've decided on your USE flags, add them to\n"
"<path>/etc/portage/package.use</path>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:136
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example: adding USE flags"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:137
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>echo \"x11-wm/fluxbox -gnome -kde truetype vim-syntax\" >> /etc/portage/package.use</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:141
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"It is also necessary to have a program lock the X display to prevent\n"
"unauthorized access, so it would be wise to also emerge <c>xlockmore</c>. The\n"
"vast majority of users will also want the ability to set their own background,\n"
"so we will emerge <c>eterm</c>, which doubles as a nice X11 terminal.\n"
msgstr ""
"また、認証されていないアクセスを防ぐためにXディスプレイをロックするプログラムも必要になるので、<c>xlock</c>をemergeするのが賢明でしょう。\n"
"圧倒的大多数のユーザは自分用の背景を設定できる機能も欲しいでしょうから、X11ターミナルの二倍良い<c>eterm</c>もemergeしましょう。\n"

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:147
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Emerging Fluxbox"
msgstr "Fluxboxをemergeする"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:148
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>emerge fluxbox xlockmore eterm</i>\n"
msgstr "# <i>emerge fluxbox xlockmore x11-terms/eterm</i>\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:152
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Well, that's it; Fluxbox is now installed! However, it is likely that you will\n"
"not be able to use it efficiently with just those tools. The following sections\n"
"will help install other potentially necessary packages, and configure Fluxbox\n"
"and the third party programs to work for you. Keep in mind that all these steps\n"
"are optional, so feel free to pick and choose.\n"
msgstr ""
"というわけで、Fluxboxがインストールされました！\n"
"でも、これらのツールだけではFluxboxを効果的に利用できそうにありません。\n"
"次のセクションでは、そのうち必要になるような他のパッケージのインストールを支援し、Fluxboxやサードパーティ製プログラムを設定しましょう。\n"
"これらすべてのステップは自由選択であることを心に留め、自由に選りすぐってください。\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:165
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring Fluxbox"
msgstr "Fluxboxの設定"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:167
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Preparing X11"
msgstr "X11の準備"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:171
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Fluxbox is simply another program that X11 runs. If desired, one can\n"
"<c>startx</c> and then type <c>fluxbox</c> at an xterm. However, this is\n"
"annoying to say the least. If one does not desire to boot to the GUI, but\n"
"instead wants to start X11 manually, it is possible to have X automatically\n"
"load Fluxbox by executing, as a normal (non-root) user:\n"
msgstr ""
"Fluxboxは、X11上で動作する単純なプログラムです。\n"
"もしお望みなら、<c>startx</c>し、それからxtermで<c>fluxbox</c>とタイプしてください。\n"
"でも、これは何と言っても煩わしいです。\n"
"GUIでブートせずにX11を手動で起動したいなら、(rootでない)一般ユーザとして実行するとXが自動的にFluxboxをロードすることができます。\n"

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:178
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Editing your xinit"
msgstr "xinitの編集"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:179
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "$ <i>echo \"exec startfluxbox\" > ~/.xinitrc</i>\n"
msgstr "$ <i>echo fluxbox > ~/.xinitrc</i>\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:183
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This is also not ideal for most users, as they want to have the desktop\n"
"environment all the time; it is a pain to <c>startx</c> if it is desired to use\n"
"a GUI everytime you boot. It also presents a security risk to the unaware. If\n"
"one locks the X11 display using <c>xlock</c>, but run X11 from a console, then\n"
"someone with physical access to the computer can switch to that console, kill\n"
"X11, and use your account. The only way to prevent this is to either background\n"
"X11 or run it in screen, detach the screen, and then logout of the console, a\n"
"tedious task at best. If one uses a graphical login manager, this problem does\n"
"not exist. However, you will be running X11 as root, which may be a bad thing.\n"
"There are, as of this writing, no exploits that the author is aware of for the\n"
"current version, but if one is concerned, then either not use X11 or use the\n"
"above method with screen. Note that this is not a Fluxbox issue, but affects\n"
"X11 itself.\n"
msgstr ""
"日常的にデスクトップ環境を使いたい大多数のユーザにとって、これは理想的ではありません。\n"
"ブートするたびにGUIを使いたいなら、<c>startx</c>するのは面倒でしょう。\n"
"また、セキュリティの危険性もはらんでいます。\n"
"<c>xlock</c>を使ってX11ディスプレイをロックしたものの、コンソールからX11を実行していたなら、\n"
"誰かがコンピュータに直接触ってコンソールを切り替え、X11を終了できるので、あなたのアカウントが使われてしまいます。\n"
"これを防ぐ唯一の方法は、X11をバックグラウンドあるいは画面で実行し、その画面を切り離してからコンソールをログアウトするというせいぜい退屈な仕事です。\n"
"グラフィカルログインマネージャを使う場合、この問題はありません。\n"
"しかし、rootとしてX11を実行する場合には悪い面が出るかもしれません。\n"
"このガイドの執筆時には、現在のバージョンに関する脆弱性について著者は存じておりませんが、もし何か関連があれば、X11を使用しないもしくは画面で上記の方法を利用してください。\n"
"これはFluxboxの問題ではなく、X11自身の問題であることに注意してください。\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:204
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"There are a number of graphical login managers to choose from; we will be using\n"
"<uri link=\"http://slim.berlios.de\">SLiM</uri>. You may use another manager at\n"
"your option, but SLiM works well for Fluxbox, as well as any other environments\n"
"you may have installed such as GNOME, KDE, or Xfce.\n"
msgstr ""
"選べるグラフィカルログインマネージャはたくさんありますが、その中でもgdmを使うことになるでしょう。\n"
"他のログインマネージャを使うのも自由ですが、他のあらゆるウインドウマネージャ(GNOME、KDE、xfceなど)と同様に、Fluxboxにはgdmを使うとよいです。\n"

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:210
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
