"Mod1 s   :ExecCommand aterm -name aterm -sl 3000 -tr +sb -sr -sk -bg black -fg\\\n"
"white -fade 90 -bl -tn xterm -fn\\\n"
"-misc-fixed-medium-r-normal-*-*-120-*-*-c-*-iso8859-15 -g 116x57 -e su -\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:349
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "System Monitor"
msgstr "システムモニタ"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:353
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"It is a common desire to setup a system monitor for X11 on desktop systems.\n"
"Gkrellm is a commonly used monitor, but in the spirit of Fluxbox minimalism, we\n"
"are going to use a simpler monitor: <c>conky</c>. If desired, use another\n"
"monitor; there are plenty of HOWTOs elsewhere.\n"
msgstr ""
"デスクトップシステムでX11用のシステムモニタをセットアップするのは共通の願いです。\n"
"一般によく使われるモニタはGkrellmですが、Fluxboxの最小化の精神から、さらにシンプルなモニタであるTorsmoを使うつもりです。\n"
"お望みなら、別のモニタを使ってください。\n"
"手引きは、そこらじゅうにいくらでもあります。\n"

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:359
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Installing conky"
msgstr "ideskのインストール"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:360
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>emerge conky</i>\n"
msgstr "# <i>emerge idesk</i>\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:364
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The default config file for Conky is rather weak, but more info can be found by\n"
"reading the manpage or the <uri link=\"/doc/en/conky-howto.xml\">Gentoo Linux\n"
"Conky Howto</uri>.\n"
msgstr "Torsmoのデフォルトの設定ファイルはかなり貧弱です。詳しい情報はmanを読むか、この<uri link=\"http://torsmo.sourceforge.net/readme.php\">readme</uri>で見つけてください。\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:372
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Icons"
msgstr "アイコン"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:376
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Fluxbox does not come with a utility or program to draw icons to the desktop;\n"
"everything is handled by keyboard shortcuts, or the right-click menu. iDesk is a\n"
"program that can be used to fulfill this need. It is aimed at users of minimal\n"
"WMs like ourselves who want to display icons in the root window, and it even\n"
"supports funky graphic effects like transparency! Despite its name, iDesk is\n"
"not affiliated with Apple or Mac (to the best of the author's knowledge).\n"
"Installing iDesk is as simple as:\n"
msgstr ""
"Fluxboxは、デスクトップにアイコンを描画するユーティリティやプログラムを搭載していません。\n"
"キーボードのショートカットか、右クリックメニューですべての処理を行います。\n"
"そこで、アイコンを生成するプログラムが利用できます。\n"
"ideskは、その名にもかかわらずAppleやMacとは関係ありません(著者の知る限りですが)。\n"

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:385
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Installing idesk"
msgstr "ideskのインストール"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:386
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>emerge idesk</i>\n"
msgstr "# <i>emerge idesk</i>\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:395
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Once installed, it will be necessary to configure iDesk so that it is able to\n"
"display the icons we desire. Its configuration file can be found at\n"
"<path>~/.ideskrc</path>. This is a rather lengthy task, and can't be well\n"
"covered in this guide. The following resources might be useful in order to help\n"
"you configure iDesk: <c>man idesk</c>, <uri\n"
"link=\"http://idesk.sourceforge.net/wiki/index.php/Idesk-usage\">iDesk's Usage\n"
"Guide</uri> and this <uri\n"
"link=\"http://forums.gentoo.org/viewtopic-t-87262.html\">thread in the Gentoo\n"
"Forums</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""
"インストールが完了すると、このプログラムにアイコンを追加する必要があるでしょう。\n"
"ideskのアイコンは、<path>~/.ideskrc</path>という設定ファイルで処理します。\n"
"設定はかなり長い仕事になりますので、このガイドの範囲に収めることはできません。\n"
"詳しい情報は、<c>man idesk</c>とするか、<uri link=\"http://idesk.sourceforge.net/usage.html\">利用ガイド</uri>を見てください。\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:409
#, no-wrap
msgid "Graphical File Manager Options"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:413
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"It is important to note that Gentoo does not need a file manager. It is\n"
"perfectly possible, and indeed simpler (in the author's humble opinion), to do\n"
"all the file manipulation by command-line. However, not everyone agrees...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:419
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Many users who are new to Gentoo/Fluxbox are put off by the lack of a graphical\n"
"file manager such as <c>nautilus</c> in Gnome. Fluxbox itself does not provide\n"
"such a program, but as always, it is simple to acquire one. There are many\n"
"choices, but this guide will present three, one for the <uri\n"
"link=\"#gentoo\">minimalist</uri> who likes text only and two for the user who\n"
"likes <uri link=\"#rox\">icons</uri> to <uri link=\"#thunar\">click</uri>. It is\n"
"also possible, of course, to install all three and try them out.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:431
#, no-wrap
msgid "Gentoo File Manager - Minimalism"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:435
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Gentoo is a file manager which seeks to provide the benefits of a GUI interface\n"
"without all the bloat which is commonly associated with such interfaces.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:439
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Installing the Gentoo File Manager"
msgstr "スタイルとアートワークのインストール"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:440
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>emerge gentoo</i>\n"
msgstr "# <i>emerge torsmo</i>\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:444
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The Gentoo file manager is a separate project from the Gentoo Linux\n"
"distribution. For more information on this, see the Gentoo <uri\n"
"link=\"/main/en/name-logo.xml#doc_chap4\">Name and Logo Usage Guidelines</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:450
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The Gentoo file manager aims to be fully configurably via GUI, so feel free to\n"
"tweak.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:458
#, no-wrap
msgid "Rox File Manager - Includes Icons"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:462
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Rox is a file manager which uses icons as well as text and is much more like\n"
"Windows' Explorer.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:466
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Installing the Rox File Manager"
msgstr "スタイルとアートワークのインストール"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:467
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>emerge rox</i>\n"
msgstr "# <i>emerge torsmo</i>\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/fluxbox-config.xml:471
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Rox behaves much like \"traditional\" file managers, so its interface\n"
"should be intuitive. If not, there always are manpages.\n"
